net.sf.JRecord.Types

Interface Type

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TypeBinBigEndian, TypeBinLittleEndian, TypeBit, TypeChar, TypeCharNullTerminated, TypeCharPadded, TypeCharRestOfFixedRecord, TypeCharRestOfRecord, TypeCommaDecimalPoint, TypeDecimalHex, TypeFjZoned, TypeFloat, TypeNum, TypeNumAnyDecimal, TypePackedDecimal, TypeRmComp, TypeRmCompPositive, TypeSignSeparate, TypeZoned

    public interface Type
    A "Type" is the interface between the raw data in the file and the internal format (what is to be displayed on the screen in the RecordEditor). A "Type" class needs to perform all conversions between how a field is stored in a file and Java Strings for display on the screen.
    Version:
    0.55
    Author:
    Bruce Martin

      • formatValueForRecord

        java.lang.String formatValueForRecord(IFieldDetail field,
                                    java.lang.String val)
        Format a value for storing in the record, it has 3 uses
        1. Format the string for storing in a record.
        2. Format for storing as a String in a comma / tab delimited files.
        3. Validate a value
        Parameters:
        field - field definition
        val - value to be formated
        Returns:
        value value as it is store in the record
